  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into thin wedges</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a matching lid, with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion wedges</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the onion has softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>ras el hanout</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant – this is your <strong>spiced onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1674811908089-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1674811908089-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1674811908089-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1674811908089-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1674811908089-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, boil half a kettle</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> roughly</p><p>Drain and rinse the <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Once fragrant, remove the pan from the heat and transfer 1/3 of the <strong>spiced onion</strong> to a medium-sized pot with a matching lid</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1674811915553-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1674811915553-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1674811915553-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1674811915553-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1674811915553-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to the pot with the spiced onion</p><p>Add 225ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to the pot with<strong> </strong>the <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked, then remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) until serving – this is your <strong>turmeric rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1674811922811-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1674811922811-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1674811922811-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1674811922811-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1674811922811-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, return the pan with spiced onion to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>grated carrot</strong> to the pan with the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong> and <strong>chopped tomato</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Season with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 7-8 min or until the tomato is starting to break down</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1674811950203-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1674811950203-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1674811950203-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1674811950203-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1674811950203-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the tomato has broken down, add the <strong>veg stock</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>Moroccan-style stew</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
